Inheritance
=======================================
Inheritance is a basic concept of OOP which will allow to use parent class features.
Using inheritance can use parent class variables and methods using child class object.

***FACTS***
Inheritance is used for:
-- Code re-usability
-- No code duplication
-- For method overriding

****INTERVIEW QUESTIONS****
-- Child class reference and Child class object --> all the methods of Base and Child class
-- Base class reference and Base class object --> all the methods of Base class only
-- Base class reference and Child class object --> all the methods of Base class only